<div class="qa-card">
  <div class="qa-q"><div class="qnum">1</div>Discuss the Role and Activities of an Accountant in a Modern Business Organisation. Also explain the Organisational Structure for the Accounting Function.</div>
  <div class="qa-a">
    <strong>I. Roles of an Accountant:</strong><br><br>
    An accountant performs three key roles:<br>
    <table>
      <tr><th>Role</th><th>Description</th><th>Example</th></tr>
      <tr><td>Score-keeping</td><td>Data accumulation / record-keeping</td><td>Preparing Balance Sheets, P&L A/c</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Attention-directing</td><td>Flagging unfavorable variances</td><td>Budget vs Actual comparison report</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Problem-solving</td><td>Comparative analysis for decisions</td><td>Make-or-buy analysis, project appraisal</td></tr>
    </table><br>
    <strong>II. Activities of an Accountant:</strong>
    <ul class="list">
      <li><strong>Recordative:</strong> Bookkeeping – journal entries, ledger posting</li>
      <li><strong>Interpretative:</strong> Budget preparation, performance analysis, funds flow, financial forecasts, capital project analysis, merger/takeover analysis</li>
      <li><strong>Auditive:</strong> Verification of transactions and authentication of financial statements (internal and external audit)</li>
      <li><strong>Data Reporting:</strong> Preparing external reports (annual reports) and internal management reports</li>
    </ul>
    <strong>III. Difference: Management Accounting vs Financial Accounting:</strong>
    <table>
      <tr><th>Point</th><th>Management Accounting</th><th>Financial Accounting</th></tr>
      <tr><td>Purpose</td><td>Decision-making by management</td><td>Reporting to external stakeholders</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Users</td><td>Internal (managers)</td><td>External (shareholders, govt)</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Format</td><td>No fixed format</td><td>Fixed (as per law / GAAP)</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Time Focus</td><td>Future-oriented (budgets)</td><td>Historical (past transactions)</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Mandatory?</td><td>Not mandatory</td><td>Mandatory (legal requirement)</td></tr>
    </table><br>
