    <ul class="list">
      <li><strong>Step 1:</strong> Collect source documents (invoices, bills, receipts)</li>
      <li><strong>Step 2:</strong> Journalize – record in Journal with Dr./Cr. and narration</li>
      <li><strong>Step 3:</strong> Post to Ledger – transfer entries to respective T-accounts</li>
      <li><strong>Step 4:</strong> Prepare Trial Balance – verify Dr. total = Cr. total</li>
      <li><strong>Step 5:</strong> Adjusting Entries – accruals (outstanding), deferrals (prepaid), depreciation</li>
      <li><strong>Step 6:</strong> Prepare Financial Statements – P&L Account, Balance Sheet</li>
      <li><strong>Step 7:</strong> Closing Entries – close temporary accounts (revenues, expenses) to zero</li>
      <li><strong>Step 8:</strong> Post-closing Trial Balance – start new accounting period with opening balances</li>
    </ul>
