<div class="qa-card">
  <div class="qa-q"><div class="qnum">1</div>Explain the Cash Flow Statement in detail with its construction, format, and comparison with Fund Flow Statement.</div>
  <div class="qa-a">
    <strong>I. Definition & Purpose:</strong><br>
    A <span class="key-term">Cash Flow Statement</span> is a financial statement that shows cash receipts (inflows) and cash payments (outflows) during a period. It is prepared as per <strong>AS-3 (Accounting Standard 3)</strong> / IND AS-7.<br><br>
    <strong>II. Important Definitions (AS-3):</strong>
    <ul class="list">
      <li><em>Cash:</em> Cash in hand and demand deposits with banks</li>
      <li><em>Cash Equivalents:</em> Short-term, highly liquid investments (e.g., treasury bills)</li>
      <li><em>Cash Flows:</em> Inflows and outflows of cash and cash equivalents</li>
      <li><em>Operating Activities:</em> Principal revenue-generating activities</li>
      <li><em>Investing Activities:</em> Acquisition and disposal of long-term assets</li>
      <li><em>Financing Activities:</em> Activities that change equity capital and borrowings</li>
    </ul>
    <strong>III. Cash Flow Statement Format:</strong>
    <table>
      <tr><th>Particulars</th><th>₹</th></tr>
      <tr><td colspan="2" style="color:var(--accent);font-weight:700">A. CASH FLOWS FROM OPERATING ACTIVITIES</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Net Profit before tax</td><td>XX</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Add: Non-cash charges (Depreciation)</td><td>XX</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Add: Non-operating charges (Interest paid)</td><td>XX</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Less: Non-operating incomes (Interest/Dividend received)</td><td>(XX)</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Working Capital Adjustments:</td><td></td></tr>
      <tr><td>&nbsp;(Increase)/Decrease in Debtors</td><td>XX</td></tr>
      <tr><td>&nbsp;(Increase)/Decrease in Inventory</td><td>XX</td></tr>
      <tr><td>&nbsp;Increase/(Decrease) in Creditors</td><td>XX</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Less: Tax Paid</td><td>(XX)</td></tr>
      <tr><td><strong>Net Cash from Operating Activities (A)</strong></td><td><strong>XX</strong></td></tr>
      <tr><td colspan="2" style="color:var(--accent2);font-weight:700">B. CASH FLOWS FROM INVESTING ACTIVITIES</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Purchase of Fixed Assets</td><td>(XX)</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Sale of Fixed Assets</td><td>XX</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Purchase/Sale of Investments</td><td>XX</td></tr>
      <tr><td><strong>Net Cash from Investing Activities (B)</strong></td><td><strong>XX</strong></td></tr>
      <tr><td colspan="2" style="color:var(--accent3);font-weight:700">C. CASH FLOWS FROM FINANCING ACTIVITIES</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Issue of Shares/Debentures</td><td>XX</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Repayment of Loans</td><td>(XX)</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Dividends Paid</td><td>(XX)</td></tr>
      <tr><td><strong>Net Cash from Financing Activities (C)</strong></td><td><strong>XX</strong></td></tr>
      <tr><td><strong>Net Increase/Decrease in Cash (A+B+C)</strong></td><td><strong>XX</strong></td></tr>
      <tr><td>Opening Cash Balance</td><td>XX</td></tr>
      <tr><td><strong>Closing Cash Balance</strong></td><td><strong>XX</strong></td></tr>
    </table>
    <br>
    <strong>IV. Comparison: Funds Flow vs Cash Flow Statement</strong>
    <table>
      <tr><th>Point</th><th>Funds Flow Statement</th><th>Cash Flow Statement</th></tr>
      <tr><td>Basis</td><td>Working Capital (broader concept)</td><td>Cash only (narrower concept)</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Governed by</td><td>No specific AS (old practice)</td><td>AS-3 / IND AS-7</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Shows</td><td>Changes in working capital</td><td>Changes in cash and cash equivalents</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Scope</td><td>Covers long-term + working capital changes</td><td>Covers only cash transactions</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Usefulness</td><td>Long-term financial planning</td><td>Short-term cash management</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Includes</td><td>Depreciation is added back</td><td>Depreciation added back (non-cash)</td></tr>
    </table>
  </div>
</div>

