    <strong>II. Utility of Ratio Analysis:</strong>
    <ul class="list">
      <li><em>Credit Analysis:</em> Creditors use liquidity ratios to assess short-term repayment capacity</li>
      <li><em>Competitive Analysis:</em> Compare with industry averages and competitors</li>
      <li><em>Trend Analysis:</em> Compare ratios over multiple years to spot performance trends</li>
      <li><em>Investment Analysis:</em> Investors use P/E, EPS, ROE to decide on investments</li>
      <li><em>Activity Control:</em> Management uses turnover ratios to control asset use efficiency</li>
    </ul>
    <strong>III. Diagnostic Role of Ratios:</strong>
    <table>
      <tr><th>Problem</th><th>Diagnostic Ratio</th><th>Ideal Signal</th></tr>
      <tr><td>Can firm pay short-term debts?</td><td>Current Ratio</td><td>&gt; 2:1</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Can firm pay without selling stock?</td><td>Quick Ratio</td><td>&gt; 1:1</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Is firm over-leveraged?</td><td>Debt-Equity Ratio</td><td>&lt; 1:1</td></tr>
